Reasoning: The paper discusses the impact of AI on the job market and proposes a fairer paradigm for AI systems. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed paradigm involves human interaction with AI systems, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of learning algorithms, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The discussion of the ethical implications of AI could also place the paper in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to AI that involves rewarding knowledge producers, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
